name: Rice Cooker Crawfish Tails
author: KIMMYLEW
summary: For those days when you only have a little bit of time and patience to cook, this recipe will fulfill your needs. It combines crawfish, spicy diced tomatoes, and rice for a quick and delicious meal. Serve with garlic bread on side. YUMMY!
ingredients: 1 ½ cups uncooked long grain rice
1 (10 ounce) can diced tomatoes with green chile peppers
1 teaspoon Cajun seasoning, or to taste
directions: In a large bowl, combine rice, green pepper, onion, green onions, crawfish tails, chicken broth, diced tomatoes, margarine, parsley, and Cajun seasoning
Pour into rice cooker, and cook for 1 cycle, or until liquid is absorbed, about 30 minutes
